            "answer_text": "My knowledge is extremely limited in this subject matter, so I\u2019ll try my best. As far as I can tell, there have been no large scale conflicts between the 3 groups. However, it should also be noted that the Triads are a LOT looser in organization to the Mafia and the Yakuza, especially the lower you get into their organization. Though perhaps the documentaries in prison life in North America (which seems to be dominated by a lot of Hispanics, no racism intended) might shed some light to their political dynamics; the dominant faction is the one with the largest bodies in any given area, and everyone else toe the line in a tense truce of sorts. I\u2019m assuming the 3 groups have their own specific spheres of influence, and usually try not to intrude into each other\u2019s territory. Any scuffles are most likely resolved diplomatically, and/or happen so deep in society\u2019s underbelly that we\u2019ll never really know (could be more horrifying than we imagined, or perhaps extremely mundane). Last thing they want is too much publicity. I suppose it\u2019s like the empires of old, who often had to consider politics and logistics in every operation. ",
