            "answer_text": "Despite what movies and television might have you believe criminal organizations actually tend to shy away from overt violent action. They want to make money and they know that open Warfare with another criminal organization would lead to increased scrutiny from law enforcement. Real-life Mobsters who have watched The Sopranos highlighted a specific line from one episode they said was 100% accurate. \u201cYou wanna go to the mattresses or you wanna make money?\u201d Going to the mattresses is a phrase meaning go to war. Basically the boss is asking another mobster if he would rather go to war or make money. And he's asking it rhetorically since clearly both of them would much rather make money than fight a war ",
